HierarchicalRequirement.Description: All data rules are based on the appropriate operational definition and formula found in the KPI master.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Data Rules

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: All calculations are based on the appropriate operational definition and formula found in the KPI master.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Calculations

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: An online Tableau report that represents data as an SPC chart and indicates when standard SPC rules have been violated as documented here http://www.asq.org/learn-about-quality/data-collection-analysis-tools/overview/control-chart.html.  It should be possible to filter the chart to show only a particular category of the data, or combinations of categories of data, with all categories (total) being the default selection.  The chart should load quickly and it should update/refresh quickly when filters are applied.  The template should be generic enough to work with various types of data.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: SPC Chart Template

HierarchicalRequirement.Description:
On online tool/interface that allows for upload of data.  Uploaded data should should either replace/update existing table records or be added/appended as appropriate.  The tool should have access control.  Preferably, one level of access would allow for adding/appending records.  Another level of access would allow for replacing/updating existing records. 

Each uploaded record should be checked for data integrity issues.  The following are some examples, but all best practices should be applied.  Each field in each record should be the appropriate data type (numeric, text, date, etc.).  All entries in a category of hierarchy field can also be found in the appropriate category or hierarchy table.  No fields in records are blank that should not be blank.  Violation of data integrity checks should generate an error message that indicates which field or fields contain records with issues.  Successful upload should generate a success message.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Data Upload Form

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: A complete mapping of BOMA codes to GL codes to Services and Service Offerings, which is used to assign costs appropriately.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: BOMA Codes Master

HierarchicalRequirement.Description:
Definitions and other necessary metadata for all key metrics that have been approved by the SLT.  The document includes the following.
Metric Name 
Metric Type
Operational Definition 
Formula 
Polarity 
Data Source 
Data Quality
Frequency of Review
Objective(s)
Target 
Target Rationale 
Green Threshold
Yellow Threshold
Red Threshold
Metric Owner 
Metric Provider 
Hieararchies and Categorizations
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: KPI Master

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: Data tables specifically created as the combined data sets needed for SPC charts in tableau.  These tables would contain denormalized and aggregated data from multiple other tables.  The tables must reflect the most current data from the multiple other tables.  For consistency and ease of use, the SPC chart tables should have a standard structure and mostly, if not entirely, standard field names.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Internal Data Views

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: Data tables collectively should contain sufficient data to apply the data rules and perform the calculations needed to generate the metrics listed in the KPI master.  They should also contain sufficient data to apply relevant categorizations and hierarchies to the metrics, which are also noted in the KPI master.  The data tables should non-system specific to allow for possible changes in source systems in the future.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Data Tables

HierarchicalRequirement.Description: For each type of data that would need to be manually uploaded into the data mart, have a standard template/form to capture the data to upload.  The format (file type) of the template/form should a common format that could be exported from or saved as from Excel and other commonly used data tools.
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Data Import Template

HierarchicalRequirement.Description:
As a WPR Digitization Database should hold the schema for Datamart and Reports creation.

Acceptance Criteria:
Should be oracle database
Schema must available in Dev, QA and Production environments
Must have sufficient storage
Should have proper grants/permissions
Should allow views
Should allow dblinks
Allow backups
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: WPR Digitization Database

HierarchicalRequirement.Description:
As a reporting feature I need to provide initial baseline reporting at the end of soft launch and establish ongoing reporting.  Additionally provide analytics as a feedback loop for improvement of the program and or processes

Acceptance Criteria:
  • Must be US and Canada only
  • Reporting has to meet stakeholder (wpr, cbre, .....) expectations
  • Capture average wait time, average session time, average response time, did we meet SLA, agent availability rate, employee abandoned chat rate, hold time, (tool, agent, emploee) exception reporting, chat volume (30 minute intervals) 
  • Must be able to report by category by WPR service, of which agent will be mandated to identify
  • Identify the quantity work order related chat by "Facilities Case Management" category and unresolved process
  • Must be available on Jive page for stakeholders to view
  • Must be only viewable on Jive by approval only
HierarchicalRequirement.Name: Custom Reports
